<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="21" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1751,2028]" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,332,1824,1848]" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name is an adjective in neuter derived form the area where it occurs, the Alentejo province in southern 
<collectingCountry box="[254,353,1860,1884]" name="Portugal" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">Portugal</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="21" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1751,2028]" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,319,1895,1920]" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species belongs to the 
<taxonomicName box="[632,747,1895,1919]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Zodarion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="styliferum">styliferum</taxonomicName>
group. It is very closely related to 
<taxonomicName box="[1136,1254,1896,1920]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Zodarion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="merlijni">
<emphasis box="[1136,1254,1896,1920]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">Z. merlijni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
both in size and colour. Females are distinguished by the epigyne in which the median plate is about twice as long as wide and the central semi-circular rim is small.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="22" pageId="2" pageNumber="21" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1751,2028]" box="[197,526,2003,2028]" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,343,2003,2028]" pageId="2" pageNumber="21">Description.</emphasis>
Male unknown.
</paragraph>
<caption box="[151,1207,898,921]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/277158/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="22" targetBox="[500,1075,194,864]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1207,898,921]" box="[151,1207,898,921]" pageId="3" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,314,898,921]" pageId="3" pageNumber="22">FIGURES 1–2.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[320,546,899,921]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Zodarion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="3" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alentejanum">
<emphasis box="[320,546,899,921]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="22">Zodarion alentejanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 1. Epigyne, ventral view. 2. Vulva, dorsal view. Scales: 0.2 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,966,1278]" pageId="3" pageNumber="22">
Female. Total length 3.3–4.1 mm; prosoma 1.5–1.7 mm long, 0.9–1.2 mm wide. Colour. Carapace and chelicera yellow, legs yellow, sternum, coxae and femora pale, abdomen dorsally brown, laterally and ventrally pale. Epigyne: Median plate almost ellipsoid, 
<number box="[603,616,1038,1062]" pageId="3" pageNumber="22" value="2.0">2</number>
-times longer than wide, with a semi-circular rim in the centre of the posterior half of plate. The diameter of the rim is half the plate width (
<figureCitation box="[904,970,1074,1098]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 2" captionStartId="3.[151,264,898,921]" captionTargetBox="[500,1075,194,864]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[493,1084,190,872]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 2. Zodarion alentejanum. 1. Epigyne, ventral view. 2. Vulva, dorsal view. Scales: 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/277158/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="22">
Fig. 
<number box="[957,970,1074,1098]" pageId="3" pageNumber="22" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
). Vulva with triangular receptacula separated by 
<date box="[249,276,1110,1134]" pageId="3" pageNumber="22">
<number box="[249,262,1110,1134]" pageId="3" pageNumber="22" value="3.0">3</number>
x
</date>
their diameter, irregular large ducts formed as in 
<figureCitation box="[832,900,1110,1134]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 2" captionStartId="3.[151,264,898,921]" captionTargetBox="[500,1075,194,864]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[493,1084,190,872]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 2. Zodarion alentejanum. 1. Epigyne, ventral view. 2. Vulva, dorsal view. Scales: 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/277158/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="22">
Fig. 
<number box="[883,900,1110,1134]" pageId="3" pageNumber="22" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
