<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="22" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,966,1278]" pageId="3" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,350,1217,1242]" pageId="3" pageNumber="22">Distribution.</emphasis>
It has been recorded only on the sand dunes of the south-western coast of 
<collectingCountry box="[1205,1303,1218,1242]" name="Portugal" pageId="3" pageNumber="22">Portugal</collectingCountry>
. But it may occur along the southern coast too (
<figureCitation box="[549,633,1254,1278]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 18" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1944,1967]" captionTargetBox="[174,1398,205,1893]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[174,1398,193,1906]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 18. Distribution maps showing actual records (points) and predicted area of distribution (shaded). 11. A. balnearius, 12. S. reticulata, 13. Z. alacre, 14. Z. alentejanum, 15. Z. algarvense, 16. Z. atlanticum, 17. Z. cesari, 18. Z. costablancae." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/277161/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="22">
Fig. 
<number box="[602,633,1254,1278]" pageId="3" pageNumber="22" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
